## Demo API authentication and routes

<!-- PROJECT: if the project has a demo API, document the auth convention and
     routes here so agents drive it correctly instead of guessing. Example
     shape:

When you need to drive the demo API end-to-end (login → ... → poll), use these
conventions:

- **Credentials.** Source the operator's `.env.local` from inside the dev
  container — it is bind-mounted at `/workspace/.env.local` and holds
  `VH-SOLARA_DEMO_ACCOUNT`, `VH-SOLARA_DEMO_PASSWORD`, and any
  demo-side overrides. Read-tool access to `*.env` is denied on purpose; use
  bash. Do not echo or inline the values.
- **API base.** `VH-SOLARA_DEMO_API_BASE` is defined in `.env.local`.
- **Routes.** Document the key endpoints here.

Never paste `VH-SOLARA_JWT_SECRET` (or equivalent) on a command line —
log in to mint a token through the API instead.
